cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new method for transfer learning in deep networks, specifically addressing the issue of heterogeneous data with different resolutions. This problem is commonly encountered in computer vision tasks, which suggests that cs.CV is a likely sub-category. The proposed method involves selecting the best matching of layers to transfer knowledge, which involves loss functions and mathematical modeling, indicating that cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper also conducts experiments for cross-domain recognition/classification tasks, which suggests that cs.CL and cs.NE are also possible sub-categories.
